.132Z$paperclip$, $paperclip$2026-04-03T13:20:15.771Z$paperclip$, $paperclip$system$paperclip$, $paperclip$1abcacb5-9ec2-43c0-bd90-ced740110646$paperclip$, 0, NULL, $paperclip${"model":"claude-opus-4-6","biller":"anthropic","costUsd":3.0106555,"provider":"anthropic","billingType":"subscription_included","inputTokens":24,"usageSource":"session_delta","freshSession":false,"outputTokens":7732,"sessionReused":true,"rawInputTokens":33,"sessionRotated":false,"rawOutputTokens":9925,"cachedInputTokens":2860834,"taskSessionReused":true,"persistedSessionId":"37f89973-13aa-4d67-9348-c37f3203befa","rawCachedInputTokens":3496765,"sessionRotationReason":null}$paperclip$, $paperclip${"type":"result","uuid":"26a30299-ec94-4d83-b99e-d55af00b280e","usage":{"speed":"standard","iterations":[],"input_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"","output_tokens":9925,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":127247,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"server_tool_use":{"web_fetch_requests":0,"web_search_requests":0},"cache_read_input_tokens":3496765,"cache_creation_input_tokens":127247},"result":"Discord knowledge extraction complete. Here's what was ported:\n\n**Oscar** -- Full financial model (salary, €2.524/month fixed costs, €10k buffer goal, budgets, AMEX timing, transaction categories)\n\n**Rex** -- Already enriched: LinkedIn strategy, Buffer API, published posts + stats, tone rules, humanizer, weekly workflow\n\n**Nox** -- All integration configs (Picnic, Buffer, Tempo, Films, GoCardless, Smart Home, News RSS), Discord channel map, 8 cron jobs to migrate, technical lessons\n\n**PARA knowledge graph** -- Two new resource sections: discord-channels and integrations with full reference docs.\n\nAtlas, Mitch, and Tommy had minimal OpenClaw memory -- nothing significant to port beyond what's already in their Paperclip workspaces.","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"num_turns":38,"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"costUSD":2.79196625,"inputTokens":33,"outputTokens":9925,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000,"webSearchRequests":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":3496765,"cacheCreationInputTokens":127247},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"costUSD":0.21868924999999997,"inputTokens":101,"outputTokens":7172,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000,"webSearchRequests":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":1154295,"cacheCreationInputTokens":53839}},"session_id":"37f89973-13aa-4d67-9348-c37f3203befa","duration_ms":377746,"stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":3.0106555,"duration_api_ms":375566,"fast_mode_state":"off","permission_denials":[]}$paperclip$, $paperclip$37f89973-13aa-4d67-9348-c37f3203befa$paperclip$, $paperclip$37f89973-13aa-4d67-9348-c37f3203befa$paperclip$, $paperclip$local_file$paperclip$, $paperclip$712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d/23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e/30d9ecf8-ec43-4514-b401-bc9182de5510.ndjson$paperclip$, $paperclip$418450$paperclip$, $paperclip$ff403abba59ffedd724323221459a963b6344d8a6f98a3fd67e83ec12bbbc7c3$paperclip$, false, $paperclip$.\n- NO Slack, PR reviews, sprint tracking, agenda briefings.\n- Focus: home automation, OpenClaw/Discord workflow, local tooling, comfort.\n\n## My Role\n- I'm Nox, the orchestrator. I don't build (max 5 lines of code). I delegate.\n- Team workflow: Nox reviews -> creates tasks -> Builder builds -> Tommy reviews -> delivery.\n- Full Paperclip team: Nox (CEO), Mitch (CTO/builder), Tommy (QA/design), Oscar (CFO), Rex (CMO).\n- Atlas (security) not yet hired in Paperclip.\n\n## Integrations (from OpenClaw)\n- Picnic/ChefClaw: groceries + recipes for weekly meal planning. Uses `picnic-api` npm package (not MCP).\n- Buffer: LinkedIn posts via GraphQL API. Images via Imgur upload. No update mutation (delete+create).\n- Tempo: automated hour logging. Reconstruction: GitHub commits > Jira > Calendar > FAC-145 filler.\n- GoCardless: ING bank read-only (Oscar only). Financial data is private.\n- Films/Series: OMDB (movies) + TVmaze (series) for posters. Discord buttons for watchlist.\n- Smart Home: HomeWizard coffee controller + Sonos speakers.\n- News: nu.nl via RSS (blocks scraping), Reuters via Google News RSS.\n\n## Cron Jobs (from OpenClaw, to migrate)\n| Job | Schedule | Agent |\n|-----|----------|-------|\n| Webbio AI Research Digest | Mon 09:15 | Nox |\n| Webbio AI Alert Daily Scan | Weekdays 08:00 | Nox |\n| Tempo Hour Reconstruction | Weekdays 17:30 | Nox |\n| News Digest | Daily 08:30 | Nox |\n| Breaking News Scanner | Every 2h 08-20 | Nox |\n| Films & Series Digest | Fri 10:00 | Nox |\n| Rex Weekly Trend Scan | Mon 08:00 | Rex |\n| Workspace Git Sync | Daily 23:00 | Nox |\n\n## Key Technical Lessons (from OpenClaw)\n- MCP servers as one-shot calls are extremely slow (Node startup + auth per call). Use underlying library directly.\n- Picnic 2FA codes expire fast -- must verify in same login session.\n- Discord buttons: type \"actions\" works, \"buttons\" doesn't. Need `reusable: true`.\n- yt-dlp needs `--impersonate chrome` for YouTube. Thumbnail check for video existence.\n- Gateway stability: Slack WebSocket caused crashes. Discord-only is stable.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":737,"cache_read_input_tokens":134541,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":737},"output_tokens":72,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37f89973-13aa-4d67-9348-c37f3203befa","uuid":"b2f6b563-47d6-4e5d-8176-249eca8c8fd4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H8zxpjP2CcKeJf25kZD3Bn","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/joerismits/.paperclip/instances/default/workspaces/23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e/MEMORY.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37f89973-13aa-4d67-9348-c37f3203befa","uuid":"b6724258-a155-43a1-915b-65078e8b0e2e","timestamp":"2026-04-03T13:19:25.631Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/Users/joerismits/.paperclip/instances/default/workspaces/23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e/MEMORY.md","content":"# Tacit Knowledge\n\n## Joeri's Operating Patterns\n- Short, direct, no filler. Dutch directness is a feature.\n- Discord = command interface. Slack = team output. Don't mix.\n- Google Calendar doubles as todo list (solo events = tasks).\n- Only ping for urgent/unexpected things. No reminders for standups, meetings, lunch.\n- Hates hour logging, automated via Tempo cron.\n- Films/series: new releases only (2025+), IMDb 7.0+.\n- Houdt niet van pittig eten.\n- Checks if content actually works (URLs, videos, data). Catches mock data immediately.\n- Expects validation BEFORE adding items.\n\n## Design Preferences\n- Wants Linear/Vercel quality but WITH personality (pixel-art robots).\n- Strict color palette: cyan-400, emerald-400, amber-400 + slate.\n- No ALL CAPS headers, max 3 typography levels.\n- Discord: no markdown tables, wrap links in <>.\n\n## Improvement Rules (hard)\n- NO improvements about Jira, Google Calendar, or GitHub.\n- NO Slack, PR reviews, sprint tracking, agenda briefings.\n- Focus: home automation, OpenClaw/Discord workflow, local tooling, comfort.\n\n## My Role\n- I'm Nox, the orchestrator. I don't build (max 5 lines of code). I delegate.\n- Team workflow: Nox reviews -> creates tasks -> Builder builds -> Tommy reviews -> delivery.\n- Full Paperclip team: Nox (CEO), Mitch (CTO/builder), Tommy (QA/design), Oscar (CFO), Rex (CMO).\n- Atlas (security) not yet hired in Paperclip.\n\n## Integrations (from OpenClaw)\n- Picnic/ChefClaw: groceries + recipes for weekly meal planning. Uses `picnic-api` npm package (not MCP).\n- Buffer: LinkedIn posts via GraphQL API. Images via Imgur upload. No update mutation (delete+create).\n- Tempo: automated hour logging. Reconstruction: GitHub commits > Jira > Calendar > FAC-145 filler.\n- GoCardless: ING bank read-only (Oscar only). Financial data is private.\n- Films/Series: OMDB (movies) + TVmaze (series) for posters. Discord buttons for watchlist.\n- Smart Home: HomeWizard coffee controller + Sonos speakers.\n- News: nu.nl via RSS (blocks scraping), Reuters via Google News RSS.\n\n## Cron Jobs (from OpenClaw, to migrate)\n| Job | Schedule | Agent |\n|-----|----------|-------|\n| Webbio AI Research Digest | Mon 09:15 | Nox |\n| Webbio AI Alert Daily Scan | Weekdays 08:00 | Nox |\n| Tempo Hour Reconstruction | Weekdays 17:30 | Nox |\n| News Digest | Daily 08:30 | Nox |\n| Breaking News Scanner | Every 2h 08-20 | Nox |\n| Films & Series Digest | Fri 10:00 | Nox |\n| Rex Weekly Trend Scan | Mon 08:00 | Rex |\n| Workspace Git Sync | Daily 23:00 | Nox |\n\n## Key Technical Lessons (from OpenClaw)\n- MCP servers as one-shot calls are extremely slow (Node startup + auth per call). Use underlying library directly.\n- Picnic 2FA codes expire fast -- must verify in same login session.\n- Discord buttons: type \"actions\" works, \"buttons\" doesn't. Need `reusable: true`.\n- yt-dlp needs `--impersonate chrome` for YouTube. Thumbnail check for video existence.\n- Gateway stability: Slack WebSocket caused crashes. Discord-only is stable.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":8,"oldLines":6,"newStart":8,"newLines":8,"lines":[" - Hates hour logging, automated via Tempo cron."," - Films/series: new releases only (2025+), IMDb 7.0+."," - Houdt niet van pittig eten.","+- Checks if content actually works (URLs, videos, data). Catches mock data immediately.","+- Expects validation BEFORE adding items."," "," ## Design Preferences"," - Wants Linear/Vercel quality but WITH personality (pixel-art robots)."]},{"oldStart":23,"oldLines":12,"newStart":25,"newLines":33,"lines":[" ## My Role"," - I'm Nox, the orchestrator. I don't build (max 5 lines of code). I delegate."," - Team workflow: Nox reviews -> creates tasks -> Builder builds -> Tommy reviews -> delivery.","-- OpenClaw had: Nox (CEO), Mitch (CTO/builder), Tommy (QA), Oscar (CFO), Rex (CMO), Atlas (security).","-- Now migrating this org structure to Paperclip. Full cutover for migrated things.","+- Full Paperclip team: Nox (CEO), Mitch (CTO/builder), Tommy (QA/design), Oscar (CFO), Rex (CMO).","+- Atlas (security) not yet hired in Paperclip."," "," ## Integrations (from OpenClaw)","-- Picnic/ChefClaw: groceries and recipes for weekly meal planning. Don't forget this one.","-- Mission Control: mostly replaced by Paperclip. Financial dashboard + recipe features stay.","-- Discord knowledge (especially Rex's social media/LinkedIn channel) is valuable and may not be fully captured in OpenClaw memory. Extract before cutover.","-- Tempo: automated hour logging for Joeri (he hates it). Weekday 17:30 cron.","-- Jira: webbiohq.atlassian.net. GitHub: JoeriSmits, org webbio.","+- Picnic/ChefClaw: groceries + recipes for weekly meal planning. Uses `picnic-api` npm package (not MCP).","+- Buffer: LinkedIn posts via GraphQL API. Images via Imgur upload. No update mutation (delete+create).","+- Tempo: automated hour logging. Reconstruction: GitHub commits > Jira > Calendar > FAC-145 filler.","+- GoCardless: ING bank read-only (Oscar only). Financial data is private.","+- Films/Series: OMDB (movies) + TVmaze (series) for posters. Discord buttons for watchlist.","+- Smart Home: HomeWizard coffee controller + Sonos speakers.","+- News: nu.nl via RSS (blocks scraping), Reuters via Google News RSS.","+","+## Cron Jobs (from OpenClaw, to migrate)","+| Job | Schedule | Agent |","+|-----|----------|-------|","+| Webbio AI Research Digest | Mon 09:15 | Nox |","+| Webbio AI Alert Daily Scan | Weekdays 08:00 | Nox |","+| Tempo Hour Reconstruction | Weekdays 17:30 | Nox |","+| News Digest | Daily 08:30 | Nox |","+| Breaking News Scanner | Every 2h 08-20 | Nox |","+| Films & Series Digest | Fri 10:00 | Nox |","+| Rex Weekly Trend Scan | Mon 08:00 | Rex |","+| Workspace Git Sync | Daily 23:00 | Nox |","+","+## Key Technical Lessons (from OpenClaw)","+- MCP servers as one-shot calls are extremely slow (Node startup + auth per call). Use underlying library directly.","+- Picnic 2FA codes expire fast -- must verify in same login session.","+- Discord buttons: type \"actions\" works, \"buttons\" doesn't. Need `reusable: true`.","+- yt-dlp needs `--impersonate chrome` for YouTube. Thumbnail check for video existence.","+- Gateway stability: Slack WebSocket caused crashes. Discord-only is stable."]}],"originalFile":"# Tacit Knowledge\n\n## Joeri's Operating Patterns\n- Short, direct, no filler. Dutch directness is a feature.\n- Discord = command interface. Slack = team output. Don't mix.\n- Google Calendar doubles as todo list (solo events = tasks).\n- Only ping for urgent/unexpected things. No reminders for standups, meetings, lunch.\n- Hates hour logging, automated via Tempo cron.\n- Films/series: new releases only (2025+), IMDb 7.0+.\n- Houdt niet van pittig eten.\n\n## Design Preferences\n- Wants Linear/Vercel quality but WITH personality (pixel-art robots).\n- Strict color palette: cyan-400, emerald-400, amber-400 + slate.\n- No ALL CAPS headers, max 3 typography levels.\n- Discord: no markdown tables, wrap links in <>.\n\n## Improvement Rules (hard)\n- NO improvements about Jira, Google Calendar, or GitHub.\n- NO Slack, PR reviews, sprint tracking, agenda briefings.\n- Focus: home automation, OpenClaw/Discord workflow, local tooling, comfort.\n\n## My Role\n- I'm Nox, the orchestrator. I don't build (max 5 lines of code). I delegate.\n- Team workflow: Nox reviews -> creates tasks -> Builder builds -> Tommy reviews -> delivery.\n- OpenClaw had: Nox (CEO), Mitch (CTO/builder), Tommy (QA), Oscar (CFO), Rex (CMO), Atlas (security).\n- Now migrating this org structure to Paperclip. Full cutover for migrated things.\n\n## Integrations (from OpenClaw)\n- Picnic/ChefClaw: groceries and recipes for weekly meal planning. Don't forget this one.\n- Mission Control: mostly replaced by Paperclip. Financial dashboard + recipe features stay.\n- Discord knowledge (especially Rex's social media/LinkedIn channel) is valuable and may not be fully captured in OpenClaw memory. Extract before cutover.\n- Tempo: automated hour logging for Joeri (he hates it). Weekday 17:30 cron.\n- Jira: webbiohq.atlassian.net. GitHub: JoeriSmits, org webbio.\n"}}
