{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PT1YAs2EqrY6ezagi6DoQw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Joeri has a Mac Mini (home base) and a MacBook Pro. The vault is on the Mac Mini at `~/.paperclip/instances/default/vault/`. He wants to access this vault from his MacBook Pro.\n\nOptions:\n1. **Tailscale + SMB/NFS mount** — He already uses Tailscale networking (from MEMORY.md). He could mount the Mac Mini folder via SMB over Tailscale and open the vault from the mount point on the MacBook Pro.\n2. **Obsidian Sync** — Paid Obsidian feature ($8/mo or $96/year). \n\nThe real blocker here is that the vault relies on symlinks pointing to agent workspaces, and most sync solutions—whether Obsidian Sync, Syncthing, iCloud, or Dropbox—will either break those symlinks or fail to sync properly since they copy files rather than preserve the link structure. The actual workspace data lives elsewhere at `/Users/joerismits/.paperclip/instances/default/workspaces/*/`, so any solution needs to handle that relationship correctly.\n\nSince he already has Tailscale set up, the cleanest approach is to mount the Mac Mini's filesystem as an SMB share over Tailscale on the MacBook Pro, then open the vault from that network mount in Obsidian. This way the symlinks stay intact because the filesystem is being accessed directly from the source machine rather than being copied. Alternatively, he could just use screen sharing to run Obsidian directly on the Mac Mini itself.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":338,"cache_read_input_tokens":56748,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":338},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e091eb8-9d61-4487-ae34-1e20746dabd3","uuid":"99ff4763-70ef-43d1-81a5-aa139d5d8c64"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PT1YAs2EqrY6ezagi6DoQw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016PtiQJi1zLKeNAYYdoppwa","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"curl -s -X PATCH -H \"Authorization: Bearer $PAPERCLIP_API_KEY\" -H \"X-Paperclip-Run-Id: $PAPERCLIP_RUN_ID\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\n  \"status\": \"done\",\n  \"comment\": \"## Antwoord\\n\\nJa, dat kan. Je hebt al Tailscale draaien tussen beide machines — dat maakt het simpel.\\n\\n### Optie 1: SMB mount via Tailscale (aanbevolen)\\n\\nDit is de beste optie omdat de vault **symlinks** gebruikt naar agent workspaces. Een file-sync tool (iCloud, Syncthing, Obsidian Sync) kopieert bestanden in plaats van symlinks te volgen — dat breekt de vault structuur.\\n\\n**Op de Mac Mini:**\\n1. System Settings → General → Sharing → File Sharing aan\\n2. Voeg de vault folder toe: `~/.paperclip/instances/default/vault/`\\n3. Of deel je hele home folder\\n\\n**Op de MacBook Pro:**\\n1. Finder → Go → Connect to Server\\n2. `smb://<mac-mini-tailscale-ip>/joerismits` (of de share naam)\\n3. Mount verschijnt onder `/Volumes/`\\n4. Installeer Obsidian (gratis): https://obsidian.md\\n5. Open vault → kies het pad op de mount, bijv. `/Volumes/joerismits/.paperclip/instances/default/vault/`\\n\\nJe leest en schrijft dan direct op de Mac Mini. Wijzigingen zijn instant zichtbaar voor agents.\\n\\n### Optie 2: Obsidian Sync (€8/maand)\\n\\nWerkt **niet goed** voor deze vault — Obsidian Sync kopieert files en volgt geen symlinks. Je zou alleen de losse vault-bestanden krijgen, niet de agent workspaces.\\n\\n### Optie 3: Screen sharing\\n\\nAls je Obsidian liever direct op de Mac Mini draait: System Settings → Sharing → Screen Sharing aan. Verbind via Tailscale IP.\\n\\n### Kort\\n\\n**SMB via Tailscale** is de juiste keuze. Geen abonnement nodig, symlinks blijven werken, en je hebt al de networking infra.\"\n}' \"$PAPERCLIP_API_URL/api/issues/4d0dbd31-02e8-4ed4-b9b5-122b1a362058\" | python3 -m json.tool | head -5"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":338,"cache_read_input_tokens":56748,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":338},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e091eb8-9d61-4487-ae34-1e20746dabd3","uuid":"56111bda-f0ef-45bc-a121-8b342ea9c516"}
