{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JoxXM6v6Qxc9BYnGKCZfds","type":"tool_result","content":"---\ntype: daily-note\nagent: Nox\ndate: 2026-04-03\ntags: [daily]\n---\n\n# 2026-04-03 -- First Paperclip Heartbeat\n\n## Context\n- Woke up for JOEA-1: migrate OpenClaw org knowledge into Paperclip\n- This is a fresh Paperclip company (joeri.dev, 712f694b) with only me (Nox) as CEO\n- Previous OpenClaw session today already did some Paperclip API integration work (different company ID 3d439abb)\n\n## OpenClaw Audit\n- Found full OpenClaw instance at ~/.openclaw/\n- 6 agents: Nox, Mitch, Tommy, Oscar, Rex, Atlas\n- Cron jobs: research digests, news, tempo, films, coffee controller, queue worker\n- Memory: extensive PARA-style daily notes + curated MEMORY.md\n- Integrations: Discord (6 bots), Slack, Jira, GitHub, Google Calendar, Tempo, Notion, HomeWizard\n- Infrastructure: Mac mini home base, Tailscale, Grafana/OTEL monitoring\n\n## Actions Taken\n- Created PARA knowledge graph structure in $AGENT_HOME/life/\n- Stored Joeri's profile, Webbio context, joeri.dev context\n- Created MEMORY.md with tacit knowledge (preferences, patterns, rules)\n- Created migration plan on JOEA-1\n- Joeri responded: hire Mitch + Tommy first, migrate crons to Paperclip, full cutover\n- Joeri noted: missed Picnic/ChefClaw integration (groceries, recipes, weekly menus)\n- Joeri noted: Mission Control mostly replaced by Paperclip, keep financial dashboard + recipes\n- Joeri noted: Discord knowledge (especially Rex's social media/LinkedIn) is valuable, may not be in OpenClaw memory\n- Updated plan document with Joeri's decisions\n- Submitted hire requests: Mitch (CTO, 467192bf) and Tommy (Designer/QA, 7d8b001d)\n- Both pending board approval: Mitch (f53a2fd4), Tommy (ac7eae7a)\n- Both hires approved by board\n- Set up instruction files (AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, HEARTBEAT.md, TOOLS.md, MEMORY.md) for both\n- Created PARA workspace structures for both agents\n- Mitch: 467192bf, Tommy: 7d8b001d -- both idle, ready for tasks\n- Joeri asked to focus on Oscar and Rex next (most valuable assistants currently)\n- Submitted hire requests: Oscar (CFO, d1e84034) and Rex (CMO, 8db8080d) -- both Sonnet 4.6\n- Set up full workspace files for both (SOUL, HEARTBEAT, TOOLS, MEMORY, AGENTS.md, PARA structure)\n- Created 6 projects: Webbio AI Research, ChefClaw, Smart Home, Content & Brand, Financial Dashboard, Automation\n- Pending board approval for Oscar and Rex\n- Oscar and Rex approved by board\n- Rex's workspace was enriched (likely by a previous OpenClaw session): full LinkedIn strategy, Buffer API config, published post history, tone rules, humanizer guidelines\n- JOEA-1 marked done. Full 5-agent team operational.\n- Agent IDs: Nox=23bc3620, Mitch=467192bf, Tommy=7d8b001d, Oscar=d1e84034, Rex=8db8080d\n\n## Discord Knowledge Extraction\n- Joeri asked to extract all Discord knowledge\n- Read all 14 daily notes from OpenClaw workspace/memory/ (Mar 2-Apr 3)\n- Read all agent workspace MEMORY.md files (Oscar, Rex, Atlas, Mitch, Tommy)\n- Read Rex's memory flush (2026-03-27.md) -- Buffer API config, published posts, workflow, humanizer rules\n- Ported Oscar's full financial model (vaste lasten, spaardoelen, budgets, patterns) to Paperclip workspace\n- Rex's workspace already enriched (MEMORY.md + SOUL.md + life/ with LinkedIn strategy, Buffer config, post history)\n- Created PARA resources: discord-channels/summary.md, integrations/summary.md\n- Updated Nox MEMORY.md with cron jobs table, integration configs, technical lessons\n- Updated knowledge graph index\n- Key learnings ported: Picnic API, Buffer API, Discord buttons, MCP performance, gateway stability\n- Atlas/Mitch had minimal OpenClaw memory (just initialization). Tommy had design lessons already ported.\n\n## JOEA-4: Obsidian Knowledge Bank Research\n- Joeri asked to investigate Obsidian as knowledge bank (trending on X/social media)\n- Researched: Obsidian + Claude Code via MCP is the core trend (persistent AI memory via vault)\n- Finding: We already have ~80% of the pattern in Paperclip (PARA, markdown memory, daily notes)\n- Recommendation: Add Obsidian as UI-layer on top, not replacement. Our files are already compatible.\n- Created plan document on JOEA-4 with 3 phases (PoC, optimization, optional MCP)\n- Reassigned to Joeri for review\n- Joeri approved plan, reassigned JOEA-4 back to me for execution\n- Executed Phase 1: created Obsidian vault at ~/.paperclip/instances/default/vault/\n- Symlinks to all 5 agent workspaces (Nox, Mitch, Tommy, Oscar, Rex)\n- 33 markdown files browseable, graph view configured with agent color groups\n- Created Home.md welcome page\n- Created JOEA-5 (Mitch, backlog) for Phase 2: Dataview, templates, frontmatter optimization\n- JOEA-4 marked done. Joeri needs to install Obsidian to use it.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b2eac7d9-809b-4897-a700-4f733ad35424","uuid":"5681d783-ff15-4736-a9b8-1b1f07777b1a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T14:02:07.617Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"---\ntype: daily-note\nagent: Nox\ndate: 2026-04-03\ntags: [daily]\n---\n\n# 2026-04-03 -- First Paperclip Heartbeat\n\n## Context\n- Woke up for JOEA-1: migrate OpenClaw org knowledge into Paperclip\n- This is a fresh Paperclip company (joeri.dev, 712f694b) with only me (Nox) as CEO\n- Previous OpenClaw session today already did some Paperclip API integration work (different company ID 3d439abb)\n\n## OpenClaw Audit\n- Found full OpenClaw instance at ~/.openclaw/\n- 6 agents: Nox, Mitch, Tommy, Oscar, Rex, Atlas\n- Cron jobs: research digests, news, tempo, films, coffee controller, queue worker\n- Memory: extensive PARA-style daily notes + curated MEMORY.md\n- Integrations: Discord (6 bots), Slack, Jira, GitHub, Google Calendar, Tempo, Notion, HomeWizard\n- Infrastructure: Mac mini home base, Tailscale, Grafana/OTEL monitoring\n\n## Actions Taken\n- Created PARA knowledge graph structure in $AGENT_HOME/life/\n- Stor